˙ž# Bridge deploy bundle for externalChainId 0xE0000002
#   committee size = 3, threshold = 2
#   Neo verifier  = 0x1111111111111111111111111111111111111111
#   Neo registry  = 0x2222222222222222222222222222222222222222
#   Neo escrow    = 0x3333333333333333333333333333333333333333
#   Eth router    = 0x4444444444444444444444444444444444444444

Pre-flight: contracts already deployed at the addresses above? Yes [ ]
            (use neo-hub-deploy for Neo, forge create for Eth)

Step 1   register the committee on the Neo verifier:
  contract: 0x1111111111111111111111111111111111111111
  method:   RegisterCommittee
  args:
    externalChainId = 0xE0000002
    threshold       = 2
    curveTag        = 1   # secp256k1
    committeeBlob   = 0x02da022c86171bbad8799ea58c71a7cb1c42a975351ca64dc1e8576d464768eba102f7cab0d6865ae6f54e9b96940bb31721faccffc7d38ba812a62e81ccaf3e22bd02dea8dd9b7e953337f1b9e4ce5037f626de63ae5cf155ea6fe7976f3054ec7cdf

Step 2   register the verifier on the Neo registry:
  contract: 0x2222222222222222222222222222222222222222
  method:   RegisterVerifier
  args:
    externalChainId = 0xE0000002
    verifier        = 0x1111111111111111111111111111111111111111
    bridgeKind      = 1   # MPC

Step 3   wire the registry into the escrow:
  contract: 0x3333333333333333333333333333333333333333
  method:   SetRegistry
  args:
    registry = 0x2222222222222222222222222222222222222222

Step 4   register the committee on the Eth router:
  contract: 0x4444444444444444444444444444444444444444
  method:   setCommittee
  args:
    members[] = [
        0x1ba6c6d6ce04a5b403a69fd6dbf3b0154bbed10e,
        0x2b1036849fdaa17d5bd1d9e1e8709f442c211f7d,
        0xbcc1b39b251d1e571c034348d659e55adb772b95
    ]
    threshold = 2

After step 4, the bridge is live. To verify, lock 1 wei from a test
Eth account via NeoExternalBridgeRouter.lockETHAndSend and watch for
CrossChainInboundFinalized on the Neo escrow within ~1 minute.
